subSubSection.paragraph:
Ground color of dorsal surface of head, limbs and dorsum bright-yellow; transverse body and tail bands darker; lateral head and belly with bright-yellow spots; marbling of surface of limbs darker; ventral surface white to light blue (
Figs 3–4
).

We compared the new species with its 19 congeners from the
Cyrtodactylus irregularis
complex based on an examination of specimens ( Table 2 ) and data obtained from the literature (
Smith 1921 a, 1921b
